Description: Fragment of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Handle to sharp turn. Rectangular stamp with winged caduceus symbol. Clay fine buff; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Probably drawn by Petrie (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 31, 13). Name Philon. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0012.30.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0980)
